    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4075cbbf_6c8197b3",
        "filename": "ttq/internal/sweepdrivers/gaecron/gaecron.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 256,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-24T06:24:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good question. The answer is that it doesn\u0027t.\n\nRAM usage SUM(len(r.payload) for r in batch) because they are loaded at once from database.\nThus batchsize * concurrent batches suffices to limit RAM.\n\nAnd CloudTasks is able to take more QPS than this library ever intends to handle.\n\nSo, removed it entirely.",
      "parentUuid": "f32dd13f_5b792e4c",
